### Version

Yosys 0.29+11 (git sha1 0b05a6425, gcc 7.5.0-6ubuntu2 -fPIC -Os), also tested on
Yosys 0.29+11 (git sha1 f7ffd12bf, gcc 7.5.0-6ubuntu2 -fPIC -Os)

### On which OS did this happen?

Linux

### Reproduction Steps

Hi there!

I encountered an issue for both logic and arithmetic left shifts. In some cases, it looks that the output may overflow.
For example, you can take this design:
```
module top(input logic [31:0] a, input logic [31:0] b, output logic [4:0] out_data);
  assign out_data = b[5:1] << a[31:27];
endmodule
```

And a testbench like:
```
int main() {
  uint32_t a = 0x4e57633b;
  uint32_t b = 0x468e7520;
  top.p_a.set<uint32_t>(a);
  top.p_b.set<uint32_t>(b);
  top.step();
  uint32_t out_data = top.p_out__data.get<uint32_t>();
  std::cout << "Out data: " << std::hex << out_data << std::endl;
}
```

Thank you!
Flavien

### Expected Behavior

Out data: `0`

### Actual Behavior

Out data: `2000` (hex)

